OL,3,CSome schools which become integrated
OL,4,C'not achieving diversity targets'
OL,6,FResponding, the Integrated Education
OL,7,FFund (IEF) criticised an "overly rigid
OL,8,Fapproach to reasonable numbers which
OL,9,Ffails to consider the unique
OL,10,Fcircumstances facing each school
OL,11,Fshould be avoided".
OL,13,F"Whilst reasonable numbers of
OL,14,FProtestant and Catholic children are
OL,15,Fimportant to Integrated Education, so
OL,16,Ftoo are those of different cultures
OL,17,Fand religious beliefs and of none, as
OL,18,Fwell as pupils of all abilities and
OL,19,Fdiverse socio-economic backgrounds,"
OL,20,Fthey said.
OL,26,@oD@ZOUsD@RO]uD@AOU{D@dO]
